## Installation
The easiest way to install the latest version from PyPI is by using pip:
```
pip install twitcaspy
```

You can also use Git to clone the repository from GitHub to install the latest
development version:
```
git clone https://github.com/Alma-field/twitcaspy.git
cd twitcaspy
pip install .
```

Alternatively, install directly from the GitHub repository:
```
pip install git+https://github.com/Alma-field/twitcaspy.git
```

Python 3.7 - 3.9 are supported.

## Source
This library is based on:
 - [tweepy/tweepy](https://github.com/tweepy/tweepy) - Twitter for Python!
 - [tamago324/PyTwitcasting](https://github.com/tamago324/PyTwitcasting) - PyTwitcasting is a library for API v2 (Î²) of Twitcasting.

